</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_262" id="130r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Der von Basel und von Ulme <expan>frewnd<ex>en</ex></expan> und
              <expan>erb<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>bott<ex>en</ex></expan>, die yecz bey uns zu <expan>Nür<ex>emberg</ex></expan>
<expan>gewes<ex>en</ex></expan> seyn, <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> etc.</ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan>
<expan>fr<ex>eunde</ex></expan>, als ir yecz von uns <expan>geschaid<ex>en</ex></expan>
            seyt und uns <expan>gebette<ex>n</ex></expan> habt, ob wir von
              <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan>
<expan>gnedigist<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> dem <expan>römisch<ex>en</ex></expan> etc. künig icht
            meͣr <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemen</expan>, daz wir <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>frewnts<ex>chaft</ex></expan> das <expan>v<ex>er</ex>künd<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>wölte<ex>n</ex></expan>, also tun wir <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>weish<ex>eit</ex></expan> zu <expan>wiss<ex>en</ex></expan>, daz uns
                <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan> der bischof von Passaw auf hewt gesagt hat, daz seinen
                <expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan> von dem <expan>vorg<ex>enante</ex>n</expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan>
<expan>gnedigist<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> dem künig ein brief <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan>, der zu
            dem <expan>ungrische<ex>n</ex></expan> Prot geben und xiiii tag alt sey; daran sein
                <expan>künigl<ex>ich</ex></expan> gnade schreib, daz er in kürcz zu uns mayne zu
                <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan>, und darauf maynen sein gnade und
                <expan>and<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>s</expan>
<expan>gnedigist<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> des künigs ret, die denn bey uns sein,
                <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan> und <expan>and<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gute<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>frewnd<ex>en</ex></expan> der stett <expan>bott<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>zu verschr<ex>eiben</ex></expan>, <expan>wid<ex>er</ex>umb</expan> zu uns zu
                <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan>, als ir das in iren <expan>brief<ex>en</ex></expan>,
            die ewch diser <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>dien<ex>er</ex></expan> auch <expan>antw<ex>ur</ex>ten</expan> wirdt,
                <expan>eygentlich<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemen</expan> mugt. Wir <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> auch dabey
                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nomen</expan>, daz die <expan>obg<ex>enante</ex>n</expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>s</expan>
<expan>gnedigist<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> des künigs rete <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gnedige<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> den <expan>kurfürste<ex>n</ex></expan>, die bey uns
                <expan>gewes<ex>en</ex></expan> sein, auch also <expan>verschr<ex>eiben</ex></expan>
            wellen, darczu wir in <pb facs="#facs_263" id="130v"/>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>dien<ex>er</ex></expan> auch gelihen <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, die brief zu
                <expan>antw<ex>ur</ex>ten</expan>. Das <expan>v<ex>er</ex>künd<ex>en</ex></expan>
            wir <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>weish<ex>eit</ex></expan> in <expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan>. Denn wo wir
                <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>ersamk<ex>eit</ex></expan> lieb oder dienst etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>ip<ex>s</ex>a</expan> die <expan>asce<ex>n</ex>sio<ex>n</ex>is</expan>
<expan>d<ex>omi</ex>ni</expan>.</ab>
</div>
